LIMITATIONS
    - Requires Python 3 with curses support
    - Very small terminals may still be constrained despite compact UI
    - Requires internet access
    - API quota restrictions apply
    - Mouse support depends on terminal emulator support for ncurses mouse events
    - Terminal text selection and copy behavior remain terminal-emulator features
    - Drag selection is not implemented by gemini-curses
    - F3 API-key input is not persistent unless explicitly saved
    - Binary/image/video file support depends on what the selected Gemini model
      and API endpoint accept as inline_data
    - Large file upload through the Gemini File API is not implemented in this
      release
    - Ctrl+G is the sole send shortcut; F5 opens Options

